 After two successful and impactful events in Lagos and Abuja, the European Union took its message of green energy and sustainable development to the Centre of Commerce, Kano State, on the 25th of September. The event, themed ‘Renewable Energy for a Sustainable Future’, took place at the Dangote Business School, Bayero University and was well attended by foreign dignitaries, academics, industry experts, political leaders and students. <img class="size-full wp-image-1277233 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate.jpg?resize=500%2C465&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="500" height="465" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate.jpg?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate.jpg?resize=300%2C279&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate.jpg?resize=58%2C54&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate.jpg?resize=209%2C194&amp;ssl=1 209w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate.jpg?resize=140%2C130&amp;ssl=1 140w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Official poster of the event. Like the preceding editions in Lagos and Abuja, the Kano event sought to bring to the forefront of national discourse, key climate change issues while advocating renewable energy as a viable solution. Ambassador Ketil Karlsen, the Head of the European Union Delegation to Nigeria and ECOWAS, in his speech underlined the effects of climate change n in Nigeria and the contribution of the European Union towards combating it. He canvassed for closer partnership between Nigeria and the European Union to ensure the adoption of clean, affordable energy. It is noteworthy that the EU and the Kano State government successfully completed and launched the Galinja Small Town Water Scheme, providing 9,000 locals access to clean water, sanitation & hygiene. The event included an insightful panel session on ‘Climate Change and the Conflicts arising from Climate Change.’. The panellists were: Dr Murtala Badamasi (Representative of the Deputy Vice Chancellor, Academic, BUK), Dr Muhammadu Buhari (Lecturer, BUK), Ambassador Ketil Karlsen, Head of EU Delegation to Nigeria and ECOWAS, and Mr. Guillaume Audren de Kerdrel, Deputy Head of the French Mission in Nigeria. Fanen Acho, a renewable energy consultant, moderated the session. During the discussion, the speakers underscored the palpable evidence of climate change on our environment; from the change in the pattern of rainfalls to the increase in temperature and much more. They also emphasized the need for the governments to acquaint themselves with the larger impacts of climate change and make use of available resources. It was a truly enlightening discussion, as the speakers shared their wealth of knowledge with the audience. <img class="size-full wp-image-1277243 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate2.jpg?resize=540%2C960&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="540" height="960" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate2.jpg?w=540&amp;ssl=1 540w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate2.jpg?resize=169%2C300&amp;ssl=1 169w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate2.jpg?resize=33%2C58&amp;ssl=1 33w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate2.jpg?resize=109%2C194&amp;ssl=1 109w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate2.jpg?resize=73%2C130&amp;ssl=1 73w" sizes="(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px" data-recalc-dims="1" />
<img class="size-full wp-image-1277254 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate3-2.jpg?resize=540%2C960&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="540" height="960" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate3-2.jpg?w=540&amp;ssl=1 540w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate3-2.jpg?resize=169%2C300&amp;ssl=1 169w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate3-2.jpg?resize=33%2C58&amp;ssl=1 33w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate3-2.jpg?resize=109%2C194&amp;ssl=1 109w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate3-2.jpg?resize=73%2C130&amp;ssl=1 73w" sizes="(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px" data-recalc-dims="1" />  Ambassador Ketil Karlson engaging the students at the panel session with fellow speakers  Alhaji Kabiru Shehu, the Kano State Head of Service, who represented the state government, acknowledged the efforts of the EU in combating climate change and making renewable energy accessible. He also voiced the state’s support to the important causes. A major highlight of the event was the Climate Innovation Challenge, aimed at sparking up the climate change discourse amongst the students of Bayero University. This challenge encouraged students to share their innovative ideas to tackle the effects of climate change and promote environmental sustainability. Twenty-six students sent in their entries and two winners emerged- Jato Fanan Joseph and Muheeb Ridwan. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1277260" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate4-1.jpg?resize=640%2C427&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate4-1.jpg?w=1000&amp;ssl=1 1000w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/climate4-1.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, 